   Here is the 67-30 roll call by which the
Senate voted Thursday to loosen restrictions on political
activities by federal and postal workers under the Hatch Act.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' was a vote to allow federal employees to
participate more in partisan politics while off the job. A ``no''
was a vote maintain current prohibitions.
   Voting yes were 54 Democrats and 13 Republicans.
   Voting no were 0 Democrats and 30 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting. The Senate has only 99 members
since the death last month of Sen. Spark Matsunaga, D-Hawaii.
Matsunaga's successor, Rep. Daniel K. Akaka, D-Hawaii, is scheduled
to be sworn in May 16.
